DOM(Document Object Model): a representation of an HTML document created by the browser which allows JS interact with
* Browser receive the HTML file
* Browser reads HTML line by line
* Browser converts HTML into object
* Browser organizes the object into a structure
* That structure becomes DOM 

.document 
  .HTML
     .body
        .h1
        .p
Every part of the DOM is a node 

1. Parent: An element that contains another element
2. Child: An element inside another element
3. Sibling: Element at the same level